An Arizona sheriff is defending his decision to use a helicopter on Thursday that cost $650 dollars per hour to search for a missing dog.

Sheriff Joe Arpaio of Maricopa County stood behind the choice to use a helicopter to search for pooch Valor, a German shepherd mix, while speaking to KPNX.

