On Monday, the number of dead dogs grew to 21, MyFoxPhoenix reports.

That number was not immediately confirmed by the Maricopa County Sheriff's Office to MailOnline.

The affiliate station reported that investigators have not filed charges against Green Acres' owners, Jesse and Maleisa Hughes, nor Logan and Austin Flake, who were looking after the dogs when they died.

'To get search warrants you need probable cause, you need evidence, and we are doing this right, we anticipate a search warrant will be issued soon,' Arpaio told the station.

Austin Flake is the son of Senator Jeff Flake (R-AZ).

